						<div class="verses">
									<div id="vers155172" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">1</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Hiram, too, king of Tyre, sent messages offering David cedar planks and car-penters and stone-masons, to build a house for him.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155173" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">2</div>
						<div class="vers-content">No doubt could David have that the Lord had ratified his sovereignty over Israel, and made him the king of a great people.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155174" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">3</div>
						<div class="vers-content">So, in Jerusalem, he provided himself with fresh wives, and had sons and daughters born to him.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155175" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">4</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Jerusalem was the birth-place of Samua, Sobad, Nathan, Solomon,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155176" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">5</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Jebahar, Elisua, (Eliphalet),</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155177" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">6</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Noga, Napheg, Japhia,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155178" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">7</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Elisama, Baaliada and Eliphalet.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155179" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">When news reached the Philistines that David had been anointed as king of all Israel, they mustered all their forces to hunt him down, and David, hearing of it, went out to meet them.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155180" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">They had come in and occupied the whole valley of Raphaim.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155181" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">10</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Thereupon David consulted the Lord; should he attack the Philistines? Would he be given the mastery? And he was bidden go to the attack; the Philistines would be at his mercy.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155182" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">11</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And now they advanced to Baalpharasim, where David defeated them; The Lord has parted the enemyâs ranks before me, he said, as easily as water parts this way and that; so the place came by its name, Baalpharasim, The Master of the Breach.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155183" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">12</div>
						<div class="vers-content">They left their idols behind them there, and David had these burnt.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155184" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">13</div>
						<div class="vers-content">But once more the Philistines came to the attack, and occupied the Raphaim valley;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155185" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">14</div>
						<div class="vers-content">and this time, when David asked counsel of God, the answer was, Do not go to the attack; withdraw first, and then come upon them from the direction of the pear-trees yonder.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155186" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">15</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Wait till thou hearest, in the tops of the pear-trees, the sound of marching feet; then offer battle; it is a sign that the Lord marches on before thee, to smite down the army of the Philistines.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155187" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">16</div>
						<div class="vers-content">So David did as the Lord had bidden him, and he drove the Philistines before him all the way from Gabaon to Gazera.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="587">â»</a> <span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers155188" class="vers vers-inline">
												<div class="vers-no">17</div>
						<div class="vers-content">After this, Davidâs renown was noised abroad everywhere, and the Lord struck terror of him into all the nationsâ hearts.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
							</div>
